From James P Callison Subject Re Spark Plug question In article mgolden cwis Brian Golden writes The nice thing about REAL platinum plugs is that you don't have to change them very often at all I think like , miles They might cost each, but they would save for themselves in the long run My T Bird SC's manual says to replace the platinum plugs every , mi Wal Mart has Autolite platinum plugs for each Are these real platinum plugs I had Bosch platinums in my ' Fiesta and my dad had 'em in his ' Bronco note the keyword had They didn't last very long much less than , mi before they had to be replaced I agree that they weren't the greatest James James P Callison Microcomputer Coordinator, U of Oklahoma Law Center C C DISCLAIMER I'm not an engineer, but I play one at work The forecast calls for Thunder ' T Bird SC It's a hell of a thing, killing a man You take away all he has and all he's ever gonna have Will Munny, Unforgiven